Constant Field Values

TCL_PROCEDURE

private static final String TCL_PROCEDURE
Called TCL procedure within the TCL update to parse the new dimension definition. The TCL procedure calls method jpoCallExecute(ParameterCache_mxJPO, String...) with the new dimension definition. All quot's are replaced by @0@0@ and all apostroph's are replaced by @1@1@.

prepare

protected void prepare(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache)
                throws matrix.util.MatrixException
Prepares unit relation information for dimensions. While parsing current values are stored separately and must be prepared for usage and some unit information is stored in properties and must be extracted:
  • If a parsed currentUnit exists this unit is added to units.
  • If a unit has a parsed Dimension_mxJPO.Unit.currentUnitProperty this property is added to the Dimension_mxJPO.Unit.properties.
  • If the Dimension_mxJPO.Unit.properties includes settings they are extracted into Dimension_mxJPO.Unit.settings.
  • If the Dimension_mxJPO.Unit.properties includes a grouped system information the values are written into Dimension_mxJPO.Unit.systemInfos.

Overrides:
prepare in class AbstractAdminObject_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
Throws:
matrix.util.MatrixException - if preparation failed
See Also:
AbstractAdminObject_mxJPO.propertiesStack, AbstractAdminObject_mxJPO.propertiesMap

update

protected void update(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,

Overrides:
update in class AbstractAdminObject_mxJPO
Parameters:

_preMQLCode - MQL statements which must be called before the TCL code is executed
_postMQLCode - MQL statements which must be called after the TCL code is executed
_preTCLCode - TCL code which is defined before the source file is sourced
_tclVariables - map of all TCL variables where the key is the name and the value is value of the TCL variable (the value is automatically converted to TCL syntax!)
_sourceFile - souce file with the TCL code to update
Throws:
Exception - if the update from derived class failed

jpoCallExecute

public void jpoCallExecute(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                           String... _args)
                    throws Exception
The method is called within the update of an administration object. The method is called directly within the update.
  • All @0@0@ are replaced by quot's and all @1@1@ are replaced by apostroph's.
  • The new dimension definition is parsed.
  • A delta MQL script generated to update the dimension to the new target definition.
  • The created delta MQL script is executed.

Overrides:
jpoCallExecute in class AbstractPropertyObject_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
_args - arguments from the TCL procedure
Throws:
Exception - if update failed, UpdateException_mxJPO if a unit could not be removed, a default unit is changed, a modified or offset of a unit is changed
See Also:
TCL_PROCEDURE
